Senator Gbemisola Ruqayyah Saraki has declared her “unwavering support” for President Muhammadu Buhari.
The younger sister to Senate President Bukola Saraki also pledged her commitment to the success of the AP in Kwara and across the country in the 2019 elections.
She declared immediately after her brother dumped the APC and returned to the PDP.
She promised she would soon rally all her supporters and associates to begin a re-election campaign for Buhari
“All members of my political organisations including GRS Movement (GRSM); GRS Foundation (GRSF); GRS Friends on Facebook (GRSFOF); Paramount Women Forum (PWF) and GRS Grassroots Youth Movement (GRS-GYM) will begin to implement the first phase of our “Get-Out-The-Vote for PMB and APC,” he message reads in part.
“Politics is a public service to the people and we ought to conduct it with dignity, peace and love for our fellow citizens.
